postcontent: Please read the Item Characteristics for important listing details.LSB#: 170804LA03 Make: The action was made by McMillan of Phoenix, Arizona, the barrel and gunsmithing was done by the Griswold Brothers of Ventura, California. Model: G30 Serial Number: 1202175B Year of Manufacture: Modern Caliber: .300 Winchester Magnum Action Type: Bolt Action, Internal Magazine Fed Rifle with Hinged Floorplate Markings: The right side of the barrel is marked “.300 WIN. MAG.” with Griswold’s logo and “GRISWOLD BROTHERS GUNSMITHING / VENTURA, CA”. The left side of the receiver is marked with McMillan’s logo and “McMILLAN / PHOENIX, ARIZONA USA”. The butt of the grip has a sticker that reads “McM”. The recoil pad is marked “Decelerator”. Barrel Length: 24”, with threading near the muzzle; the muzzle diameter is 0.59”, the barrel, before the threading, is 0.80” in diameter and the barrel reads 1.280”. Sights / Optics: The rifle does not have provisions for iron sights, the top of the receiver has a picatinny scope base currently installed. Stock Configuration & Condition: The stock is a McMillian M40A-1 HTG (general purpose hunting) camo stock. The stock free floats roughly 21 ½” of the barrel. The inside channel is fiberglass filled to perfectly mate with the rest of the barrel and receiver portion. The sides of the forend and pistol grip have nice texturing for traction. The stock has a semi-pistol grip and fluted Monte Carlo comb. The stock shows scattered scuffs, some of which penetrate the outer paint but mostly goes unnoticed since the stock has a camouflaged pattern. There are no cracks or chip losses. The LOP measures 13 5/8” from the front of the trigger to the back of the black solid rubber shotgun-style Decelerator recoil pad; the pad is set with a black spacer and shows only light scuffs, in Excellent condition. The stock rates in about Excellent overall condition.Type of Finish: Matte Blue Finish Originality: Original Bore Condition: The bore is bright and the rifling is sharp; our bore gauge gave an M.E. of about 0.0. There is no erosion. We believe the rifling has a 1 in 10” right hand twist. There is stubborn fouling at the muzzle. Overall Condition: This rifle retains about 97% of its metal finish. Outside of a few light scuffs on the floorplate and trigger plate, there are only a few extremely faint scuffs present on the surfaces. The bolt and receiver have normal operational wear. The rifle has been well taken care of in the interim. The scope base has some light finish loss from the previous installation of scope rings. The screw heads are sharp. The markings are crisp. Overall, this rifle rates in about Excellent condition.Mechanics: The action functions correctly. We have not fired this rifle. As with all previously owned firearms, a thorough cleaning may be necessary to meet your maintenance standards. Box, Paperwork & Accessories: None Our Assessment: This is one hell of a setup! The Griswold Brothers heavy profile 24” barrel has bright, sharp rifling with an M.E. reading of about ZERO, and is free-floated the first 21”, in the camouflaged synthetic McMillan stock. The rifle is in .300 Winchester Magnum, with a spiral fluted bolt, which glides with ease. McMillan and the Griswold Brothers are two very well known and revered precision companies with a solid background in custom builds; this setup was done professionally and should make for an extremely accurate piece with the addition of your favorite optic. This rifle should ring true for long distance shooting and would be just as well suited for hunting larger game. Compared with the 30-06 Springfield the .300 Winchester Magnum provides a nearly 300 ft/s (91 m/s) increase in velocity. This translates to about 20% greater energy advantage over the 30-06 Springfield cartridge. The .300 Winchester Magnum is known for its accuracy and has been used for 1,000-yard (910 m) and 1,000-metre (1,100 yd) competitions. Some consider it the most useful and popular cartridge today. The cartridge was championed by the legendary American Sniper, Chris Kyle, who claimed it to be one of the best rounds ever made. Please see our pictures and good luck. title: For Sale:  Custom Build OD Green AR-15 HBAR Rifle
postcontent: This is a super nice looking AR15 rifle assembled with great components.  This rifle has never, ever been fired.  ADCO Firearms machine shop (The best imo) assembled the upper, barrel and FSB for me.  They test fired this assembly (Not including the BCG and Charging handle which are still unfired.) to make certain it functions.  Other than that this rifle could be considered new.All furniture is Magpul and rifle will come with three Gen 2 OD Green 30 round windowed PMAGs.  (Discontinued and not exactly easy to come by.)I started with an unused early 1990's 16" 1:9 twist .223/5.56 heavy barrel from Olympic Arms that has been saved for a very long time, these are desirable barrels from when Oly Arms was great manufacturer.  This rifle was built because I wanted to get this excellent barrel into action.  The upper receiver is a 7075 Aero Precision.  The BCG is a nitride AIM Surplus unit (I believe originally manufactured by ToolCraft.) and the charging handle is a one piece Blackhawk ambi model with no moving parts.  Rear sight is a standard gov issue A2 which is my personal favorite rear sight.  The flash hider is from Yankee Hill Machine and one of the best at masking flame belches.  Almost forgot, I installed a Strike Industries polymer ejection port cover.The 7075 forged lower is Anderson, always solid.  It's filled with a premium NiB coated mil-spec fire control group, Noveske & Magpul ambi 60 degree safety selector and a Magpul extended magazine release.  A mil-spec carbine buffer and spring round out the lower assembly.I will also include a matching OD Green QD sling.This is a great rifle, I built it to keep forever but I just never got around to shooting it and I'm not sure I ever will.  Transfer will take place at Lynnwood Gun and buyer pays fees.  I'm asking a very reasonable $700 for the rifle and the price is firm.  If you don't want the three PMAG's you can buy the rifle for $650, I wouldn't mind hanging on to these since the color is no longer available.Shoot me a line if you're interested, please include your number and I'll give you a call.  Sorry but I'm forced to assume all messages without a phone number are spam, I get a lot of those from sales ads these days.  I'll be happy to answer any questions you have when we talk.Thanks for looking.

A pistol and company that needs no introduction, absolutly one of the finest firearms made today. Local pickup only.The T3 has the best features for any gun its size.
